Five Stages of Ethical Hacking:

1. Reconnaissance, information gathering, active and passive. 

2. Scanning and Enumeration, nmap, nessus, nikto

3. Gaining Access, exploitation

4. Maintaining Access

5. Covering Tracks, cleanup, delete any logs, accounts, malware that were left behind

-------------------------------

Passive Reconnaissance:

1. Physical/social engagement, utilizing location information to see if there are badge readers, break areas, security and fencing. 

2. Job Information, utilizing employees name, job title, phone number, manager, pictures of badges, desktop photos, and computer photos.

3. Web/Host, using target validation such as WHOIS, nslookup, dnsrecon. Finding subdomains such as Google Fu, dig, Nmap, Sublist3r, Bluto, crt.sh. Fingerprinting such as Nmap, Wappalyzer, WhatWeb, BuiltWith, Netcat. Data Breaches such as HavelBeenPwned, Breach-Parse, WeLeakinfo, this is about past breaches on our targets.

